  "title": "Senior Business Performance Manager",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities</strong></u></p>\n<p>This job description outlines the responsibilities of a Business Performance Manager, who serves as a Cost Controller and Risk Management Specialist. Key aspects include:</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Key Responsibilities</p>\n<p>1. Financial Management: Oversee finance and accounting operations.</p>\n<p>2. Risk Management: Identify, analyze, and mitigate financial risks.</p>\n<p>3. Policy Development: Establish and implement Group Finance/Accounting Policies and Procedures.</p>\n<p>4. Audit and Compliance: Conduct audit checks and ensure compliance with policies, procedures, and local regulations.</p>\n<p>5. Budget Administration: Administer budgets, identify variances, and provide feedback.</p>\n<p>6. Cost Efficiency: Develop solutions to reduce costs, eliminate waste, and maximize profits.</p>\n<p>7. Financial Analysis: Analyze revenue and costs, identify trends, and provide recommendations.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Key Skills and Qualities</p>\n<p>1. Financial Expertise: Strong knowledge of finance, accounting, and risk management.</p>\n<p>2. Analytical Skills: Ability to analyze financial data, identify trends, and provide insights.</p>\n<p>3. Leadership: Ability to direct and plan financial activities, and manage finance/accounting departments.</p>\n<p>4. Communication: Strong communication skills to provide presentations, suggestions, and recommendations.</p>\n<p>5. Problem-Solving: Ability to identify and resolve accounting issues, and develop solutions to streamline work processes.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s Degree in a related field, such as Accounting, Finance, Business Administration, or Economics.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency with Microsoft spreadsheet, particularly Microsoft Excel and Access</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication skills to ensure an effective collaboration with other departments.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
